String ansascraper.Yylex.replaceSpecialCharacters ( String  input  )  [private]

Substitutes the special HTML characters eventually present in the input string, with their corresponding visual representation. To do so it uses the matrix specialCharacters.

Parameters:

Returns:

String ansascraper.Yylex.specialCharacters[][] [private]

2-columns matrix containing, for each sequence corresponding to a special HTML character, the graphical rappresentation of such character. It is used before we pass the token representing the text of a news to the syntax analyzer, to make sure that the text of the token doesn't contain sequences of the format &[qualcosa];
